title: Woman has month-long Barclays block after fake fraud claim
text: show ad Barclays customer has her account blocked for more than a MONTH after false claim that Â£90 deposit was fraudulent Laura Costello, from south east London, said her account has been blocked since the new year after a fraudulent claim of fraud The mother-of-one has been unable to withdraw compensation from sex assault She claims Barclays has never written to her and staff tell her they don't have to explain their procedures to her Barclays Bank has been contacted for a comment Published: 21:14 GMT, 7 February 2017 | Updated: 21:26 GMT, 7 February 2017 5 shares
